The paper discusses theoretical guarantees for optimizing the parameters of artificial neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on networks with piecewise affine activation functions, which are commonly used in computer vision and speech recognition applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
